name: v5.6.0
body: New features include the addition of five new Autoprotocol instructions: `agitate`, `evaporate`, `image`, `sonicate`, and `spe`.

This is a major release that implements many ASC changes and has some breaking changes.

Please refer to the docs changelog https://autoprotocol-python.readthedocs.io/en/latest/changelog.html for the full changelog.

In the future, please refer to the release tag for the latest release and to the documentation for the full changelog.

name: v4.0.0
body: This release includes added functionality to existing methods, updating code to current ASCs, new container types, and better error handling. Please see the changelog for details.

name: v3.10.0
body:
This release includes a new feature which allows developers to easily convert a protocol to a water/dye test by adding the flag: `--dye_test` when generating autoprotocol using the [Transcriptic CLI](https://github.com/transcriptic/transcriptic).

See the [changelog](http://autoprotocol-python.readthedocs.io/en/latest/changelog.html) for details.

name: v3.8.0
body: Improved documentation adhering to semantic versioning, new features and bug fixes.  See the [changelog](http://autoprotocol-python.readthedocs.io/en/latest/changelog.html) for details.

name: v3.7.4
body: This release fixes automatic uncovering before provisioning instructions.

name: v3.7.3
body: This release includes additional auto-cover steps for instructions such as incubate and new methods to `WellGroup` to increase overall functionality and usability.

name: v3.5.1
body: This release includes the addition of an optional parameter `one_tip=True` to the `Mix` instruction and a minor fix to the `AccousticTransfer` instruction.

name: v3.5.0
body: This release includes three new instructions: `IlluminaSeq`, `MeasureConcentration` and `MeasureMass`, as well as additional optional parameters to the `Spin` instruction.  See the changelog for details on minor changes and fixes contained in this release.

name: v3.4.0
body:
Added features:
- New Instruction `GelPurify` 
- `discard()` and `set_storage()` methods for `Containers`
- List compatibility to `robotize` and `humanize` methods.

name: v3.3.0
body: Add `csv-table` input type for building packages using a `manifest.json`.

name: v3.1.0
body: This release includes changes to the Unit class, using the package Pint as the base units library. The Unit.value attribute has been removed in favor of the more robust built-in unit conversions from Pint. Additions include a MagneticTransfer Instruction.
